It appears that president Uhuru Kenyatta is determined to push for a united opposition front that would defeat his deputy William Ruto in the August 9th 2022 presidential contest. The president convened a meeting bringing together former NASA principals as well as KANU chairman Gideon Moi and Kakamega Governor Wycliffe Oparanya, in a move seen by pundits as an effort to craft a winning formula.